article.description: Kelly's jumper lifts Samford over Furman 57-55
article.headline: Kelly's jumper lifts Samford over Furman 57-55
article.linkText: Kelly's jumper lifts Samford over Furman 57-55
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- Raijon Kelly made a go-ahead jumper for Samford with 11.3 seconds left and Tim Williams clinched the win with a block as time expired in a 57-55 victory over Furman Saturday night. Samford was down 55-54 with 17.9 seconds left, when Kelly took the inbounds pass from the top of the key and drove right for a 17-foot pull-up jumper. Kelly was fouled and converted the three-point play. On the other end, Stephen Croone drove under the basket and attempted a game-tying shot for Furman, but Williams rejected him as time expired for his fifth block. Tyler Hood had 13 points and Isaiah Williams scored 11 for the Bulldogs (7-12, 1/3 Southern Conference). Kendrec Ferrara led Furman (6-11, 0-4) with 20 points and Croone added 11. The game was tied nine times, the last time coming at 52-52. Croone broke the tie with a 3-pointer that put Furman up 55-52.
